N.V. Philips and Hitachi Medical Corp. said they plan jointly to manufacture computed tomography scanners in the 

The big Dutch electronics group and its Japanese partner plan to set up a facility outside Boston to produce 150 to 200 CT scanner units a year.
Hitachi will control 51% of the venture; Philips will own the rest and will supply top management. 

A Philips spokesman said the U.S. is the world's biggest market for CT scanners. 

The partners will establish a joint venture company to be called CT Scanner Manufacturing Inc., which will require about $3 million to secure a production site.
Machine tools and components to outfit the facility will be supplied from various Philips and Hitachi operations elsewhere in the world, the spokesman said. 

